    <!-- Chosen Palette: Calm Harmony Neutrals (Stone, Slate, Teal, Amber) -->
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The application is designed as a role-based interactive dashboard. This structure was chosen because the source report contains distinct sets of obligations for different parties (PCBUs, Workers, Officers). A user can immediately select their role to view tailored information, which is far more efficient than reading a linear document. The top navigation provides secondary access to cross-cutting themes like 'Key Concepts' and the 'WHS Matrix'. This dual-navigation approach supports both role-specific queries and broader exploration, maximizing usability and speed to information. Key interactions include clickable cards, accordions for progressive disclosure of dense text, and interactive diagrams to visualize processes. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Report Info: PCBU/Worker/Officer duties -> Goal: Inform role-specific obligations -> Viz/Method: Dedicated sections with interactive accordions (HTML <details> tag) -> Interaction: Click to expand/collapse -> Justification: Prevents overwhelming users with text; allows drill-down into specific duties. Method: HTML/JS.
        - Report Info: Risk Management Process -> Goal: Explain a 4-step cycle -> Viz/Method: Circular diagram -> Interaction: Hover over a step to see its description -> Justification: Visually represents the cyclical nature of the process, making it more memorable than a list. Method: HTML/CSS/JS.
        - Report Info: Hierarchy of Controls -> Goal: Show prioritized safety controls -> Viz/Method: Inverted pyramid diagram -> Interaction: Click a level to highlight and read details -> Justification: The pyramid shape intuitively communicates the concept of a hierarchy of effectiveness. Method: HTML/CSS/JS.
        - Report Info: WHS Matrix -> Goal: Compare rights/duties across domains -> Viz/Method: Grid of interactive cards -> Interaction: Click card to flip/expand for details -> Justification: More engaging and mobile-friendly than a wide, static table. Method: HTML/JS.
        - All visualizations are created using structured HTML and styled with Tailwind CSS to avoid external dependencies and adhere to the NO SVG constraint. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
